            . I am shopman to John Kinder Cheese, a <rs id="t18261026-231-viclabel1275" type="occupation">pawnbroker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18261026-231-victim1361 t18261026-231-viclabel1275"></join>, who lives at Bow. On the evening of the 5th of October I saw the prisoners at our private door; they saw me, and went away. I went and saw them there again - Peters was rolling up a pair of trousers, and Donovan was endeavouring to conceal him; they were then sitting down - I took Peters; our apprentice took Donovan, who ran away, in my sight; the trousers are master's, and were safe five minutes before.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>PETERS' Defence. I went with Donovan and two others to get blackberries - I sat down to tie my shoe, and as I got up my shoulder lifted up the trousers, and they fell.</p>
               <p>DONOVAN's Defence. I saw him lift off the trousers with his shoulder; I ran away, thinking the gentleman was coming to beat me.</p>
               <p>Donovan received a good character.</p>
